org.openbase.bco.ontology.lib.manager.aggregation

Class DataProviding

  • java.lang.Object
    • org.openbase.bco.ontology.lib.manager.aggregation.DataProviding

  • public class DataProviding
extends Object
    This class is used as information interface for the aggregation process. The information will be asked from the BCO ontology via SPARQL over HTTP (SOH). Providing data are e.g. unit-connection times, unit observations (state values).
    Author:
    agatting on 24.03.17.

    • Method Detail

      • getConnectionTimes

        public HashMap<String,Long> getConnectionTimes()
                                        throws org.openbase.jul.exception.NotAvailableException,
                                               InterruptedException,
                                               ExecutionException
        Method returns a map of connection times in milliseconds (values) for each unitId (keys). The connection times are in each case subset of the time frame, which should be aggregated. Means a connection time at most limited to the size of the duration of the time frame.
        Returns:
        a map with connection times in milliseconds (values) for each unitId (keys).
        Throws:
        org.openbase.jul.exception.NotAvailableException - is thrown in case a result parameter of the query is invalid.
        InterruptedException - is thrown in case the application is interrupted.
        ExecutionException - is thrown in case the callable thread throws an unknown exception.

      • selectConnectionPhases

        public OntUnitConnectionTimes selectConnectionPhases()
                                              throws org.openbase.jul.exception.InitializationException
        Method executes a SPARQL query via http to get all connection phases of the units from the BCO ontology. Based on the result the connection times for each unit are extracted. The data (units and their times in milliseconds) are mapped in the data type OntUnitConnectionTimes. A connection time is at most limited to the size of the duration of the time frame Interval.
        Returns:
        OntUnitConnectionTimes - a mapping of units and connection times.
        Throws:
        org.openbase.jul.exception.InitializationException - is thrown in case the data couldn't be get or mapped.

      • selectObservations

        public OntUnits selectObservations()
                            throws org.openbase.jul.exception.InitializationException
        Method selects all observations (NOT aggregated only!) from the BCO ontology by query. The result will be processed and collected into the data structure OntUnits.
        Returns:
        the data structure OntUnits.
        Throws:
        org.openbase.jul.exception.InitializationException - is thrown in case the BCO ontology isn't reachable or the processing of the result couldn't be done.

      • getObservations

        public HashMap<String,List<OntObservation>> getObservations()
                                                     throws org.openbase.jul.exception.MultiException,
                                                            InterruptedException,
                                                            ExecutionException
        Method indicates all observations of the ontology through a SPARQL query. The result is a map with the unitId as key and a list of observations as value is returned.
        Returns:
        a map with unitId as key and a list of related observations.
        Throws:
        org.openbase.jul.exception.MultiException - is thrown in case the dateTimes (from, until) could not be parsed.
        InterruptedException - is thrown in case the application is interrupted.
        ExecutionException - is thrown in case the callable thread throws an unknown exception.
